Tina Thompson, a two-year-old girl who was last week declared missing on Arab Road in Kubwa, a satellite town in Bwari Area Council of the FCT, has been found dead in Zuba in on a refuse dump around the motor spare parts market. Tina’s father, Michael, confirmed this development to our reporter on Wednesday. Windstorm kills 6, injures 65 in Jigawa Terrorists killed 14,500 persons in 4 years – ECOWAS He said, “After the news of my daughter’s disappearance went viral last week, we intensified the search. I was shocked when one of my relatives in Zuba called, saying my daughter had been found dead on a refuse dump close to the spare parts market. “I rushed there to confirm and behold I saw my daughter wrapped in a sack. Who did I offend? I mind my business. Indeed, we are in a wicked world. We need to be security conscious.” Recall that City & Crime reported how the late Tina’s parents cried out to the authorities in Abuja to help recover their daughter. 